{
  "stem": "13623.5",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "In those days, it was very shortly after the war, there was no-- no transportation.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So people either walked, traveled by horse and buggy, or any way they could.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He passed my town.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Out of the 83 families that lived in my town, there were two Jewish men in my town.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father and one other man by the name of [?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Schmiel ?] [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Stover. ?] [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] As he passed the town, my father remembered this man from-- from the ghetto, naturally the thing to ask was, did anybody survive?",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Did you see my son?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Did you see my daughter?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Did you see my wife?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Do you know if anybody survived?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This man told my father, yes, your-- your son is alive.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "He was liberated.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I left him in Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He did not know at the time that I wound up going to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Now my father knows I'm alive.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He knows I'm somewheres.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He doesn't know where.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We-- we came to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Most of us still came in our prisoner's striped clothes.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We were all full of lice.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- a lot of us were sick.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And had-- a lot of us had impetigo, that itchy type of rash.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They-- I have to say and thank the Swedish people from the bottom of my heart.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They were just a sight that we could use at that time.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were absolutely wonderful to us.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We weren't just Jewish prisoners.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "We were from all countries, all walk of life, all kinds of ages, whoever survived.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They made us undress.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Took off all our dirty clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] They put-- oh yeah.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "First they put us in a quarantine.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
